      • BaseAdGroupId

        public static final AdGroupAdField BaseAdGroupId
        ID of the base ad group from which this draft/trial ad was created. For base ad groups this is equal to the ad group ID. If the ad group was created in the draft or trial and has no corresponding base ad group, this field is null. This field is only returned on get requests.

      • BaseCampaignId

        public static final AdGroupAdField BaseCampaignId
        ID of the base campaign from which this draft/trial ad was created. This field is only returned on get requests.

      • BusinessName

        public static final AdGroupAdField BusinessName
        The business name. This field is required and should not be null when it is contained within Operators : ADD.

      • CallOnlyAdBusinessName

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdBusinessName
        Business name of the ad.

      • CallOnlyAdCallTracked

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdCallTracked
        If set to true, enable call tracking for the creative. Enabling call tracking also enables call conversions.

      • CallOnlyAdConversionTypeId

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdConversionTypeId
        Conversion type to attribute a call conversion to. If not set, then a default conversion type id is used. Only in effect if callTracked is also set to true otherwise this field is ignored.

      • CallOnlyAdCountryCode

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdCountryCode
        Two letter country code for the ad. Examples: 'US', 'GB'.

      • CallOnlyAdDescription1

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdDescription1
        First line of ad text.

      • CallOnlyAdDescription2

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdDescription2
        Second line of ad text.

      • CallOnlyAdDisableCallConversion

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdDisableCallConversion
        By default, call conversions are enabled when callTracked is on. To disable call conversions, set this field to true. Only in effect if callTracked is also set to true. If callTracked is set to false, this field is ignored.

      • CallOnlyAdPhoneNumber

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdPhoneNumber
        Phone number string for the ad. Examples: '(800) 356-9377', "16502531234", "+442001234567"

      • CallOnlyAdPhoneNumberVerificationUrl

        public static final AdGroupAdField CallOnlyAdPhoneNumberVerificationUrl
        Url to be used for phone number verification.

      • CreationTime

        public static final AdGroupAdField CreationTime
        Media creation date in the format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS+TZ. This is not updatable and not specifiable.

      • CreativeFinalAppUrls

        public static final AdGroupAdField CreativeFinalAppUrls
        A list of final app URLs that will be used on mobile if the user has the specific app installed.

        This field is used for upgraded urls only, as described at: https://developers.google.com/adwords/api/docs/guides/upgraded-urls

      • CreativeFinalMobileUrls

        public static final AdGroupAdField CreativeFinalMobileUrls
        A list of possible final mobile URLs after all cross domain redirects.

        This field is used for upgraded urls only, as described at: https://developers.google.com/adwords/api/docs/guides/upgraded-urls

      • CreativeFinalUrls

        public static final AdGroupAdField CreativeFinalUrls
        A list of possible final URLs after all cross domain redirects.

        This field is used for upgraded urls only, as described at: https://developers.google.com/adwords/api/docs/guides/upgraded-urls

      • CreativeTrackingUrlTemplate

        public static final AdGroupAdField CreativeTrackingUrlTemplate
        URL template for constructing a tracking URL.

        This field is used for upgraded urls only, as described at: https://developers.google.com/adwords/api/docs/guides/upgraded-urls

      • CreativeUrlCustomParameters

        public static final AdGroupAdField CreativeUrlCustomParameters
        A list of mappings to be used for substituting URL custom parameter tags in the trackingUrlTemplate, finalUrls, and/or finalMobileUrls.

        This field is used for upgraded urls only, as described at: https://developers.google.com/adwords/api/docs/guides/upgraded-urls

        public static final AdGroupAdField DevicePreference
        The device preference for the ad. You can only specify a preference for mobile devices (CriterionId 30001). If unspecified (no device preference), all devices are targeted.

      • Dimensions

        public static final AdGroupAdField Dimensions
        Various dimension sizes for the media. Only applies to image media (and video media for video thumbnails).

      • DisplayUrl

        Visible URL.

      • DurationMillis

        The duration of the associated audio, in milliseconds.

      • ExpandingDirections

        public static final AdGroupAdField ExpandingDirections
        Allowed expanding directions. These directions are used to match publishers' ad slots. For example, if a slot allows expansion toward the right, only ads with EXPANDING_RIGHT specified will show up there.

      • ImageCreativeName

        public static final AdGroupAdField ImageCreativeName
        The name label for this ad. This field is required and should not be null.

      • IndustryStandardCommercialIdentifier

        public static final AdGroupAdField IndustryStandardCommercialIdentifier
        The Industry Standard Commercial Identifier code for this media, used mainly for television commercials.

      • IsCookieTargeted

        public static final AdGroupAdField IsCookieTargeted
        Defines whether or not the ad is cookie targeted. (i.e. user list targeting, or the network's equivalent).

      • IsTagged

        public static final AdGroupAdField IsTagged
        Defines whether or not the ad contains a tracking pixel of any kind.

      • IsUserInterestTargeted

        public static final AdGroupAdField IsUserInterestTargeted
        Defines whether or not the ad is targeting user interest.

      • Labels

        public static final AdGroupAdField Labels
        Labels that are attached to the AdGroupAd. To associate an existing Label to an existing AdGroupAd, use AdGroupAdService#mutateLabel with ADD operator. To remove an associated Label from the AdGroupAd, use AdGroupAdService#mutateLabel with REMOVE operator. To filter on Labels, use one of Predicate.Operator#CONTAINS_ALL, Predicate.Operator#CONTAINS_ANY, Predicate.Operator#CONTAINS_NONE operators with a list of Label ids.

      • LogoImage

        public static final AdGroupAdField LogoImage
        Logo image to be used in the ad. This ad format does not allow the creation of an image using the Image.data field. An image must first be created using the MediaService, and Image.mediaId must be populated when creating a "ResponsiveDisplayAd".

      • LongHeadline

        public static final AdGroupAdField LongHeadline
        Long format of the headline of the ad.

      • MarketingImage

        public static final AdGroupAdField MarketingImage
        Marketing image to be used in the ad. This ad format does not allow the creation of an image using the Image.data field. An image must first be created using the MediaService, and Image.mediaId must be populated when creating a "ResponsiveDisplayAd".

        Impression beacon URL for the ad.

      • RichMediaAdName

        public static final AdGroupAdField RichMediaAdName
        Name of the rich media ad. This field is required and should not be null.

      • RichMediaAdSnippet

        public static final AdGroupAdField RichMediaAdSnippet
        Snippet for this ad. Required for standard third-party ads.

        The length of the string should be between 1 and 3072, inclusive.

      • RichMediaAdSourceUrl

        public static final AdGroupAdField RichMediaAdSourceUrl
        SourceUrl pointing to the third party snippet. For third party in-stream video ads, this stores the VAST URL. For DFA ads, it stores the InRed URL.

        The streaming URL of the audio.

      • TemplateAdDuration

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateAdDuration
        Duration of this ad (if it contains playable media).

      • TemplateAdName

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateAdName
        Name of this ad. This field is required and should not be null.

      • TemplateAdUnionId

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateAdUnionId
        Group ID of all template ads, which should be created together. Template ads in the same union reference the same data but have different dimensions. Single ads do not have a union ID. If a template ad specifies an ad union with only one ad, no union will be created.

      • TemplateElementFieldName

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateElementFieldName
        The name of this field.

      • TemplateElementFieldText

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateElementFieldText
        Text value for text field types. Null if not text field. The field is a text field if type is ADDRESS, ENUM, TEXT, URL, or VISIBLE_URL.

      • TemplateElementFieldType

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateElementFieldType
        The type of this field.

      • TemplateId

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateId
        ID of the template to use.

      • TemplateOriginAdId

        public static final AdGroupAdField TemplateOriginAdId
        For copies, the ad id of the ad this was or should be copied from.

      • Trademarks

        public static final AdGroupAdField Trademarks
        A list of strings that represents the specific trademarked terms that were found in this ad. The list returned is empty if the ad has no trademarked terms.

      • Type

        public static final AdGroupAdField Type
        Type of the creative.

      • UniqueName

        public static final AdGroupAdField UniqueName
        Unique name for this element.

      • Url

        public static final AdGroupAdField Url
        Destination URL.

        Do not set this field if you are using upgraded URLs, as described at: https://developers.google.com/adwords/api/docs/guides/upgraded-urls

      • UrlData

        public static final AdGroupAdField UrlData
        Additional urls for the ad that are tagged with a unique identifier. Currently only used for TemplateAds for specific template IDs. For all other ad types, use finalUrls, finalMobileUrls and finalAppUrls instead.

      • Urls

        public static final AdGroupAdField Urls
        URLs pointing to the resized media for the given sizes. Only applies to image media.

      • VideoTypes

        public static final AdGroupAdField VideoTypes
        Video Types of the ad. (RealMedia, Quick Time etc.)

      • Width

        public static final AdGroupAdField Width
        Width of the dimension

      • YouTubeVideoIdString

        public static final AdGroupAdField YouTubeVideoIdString
        For YouTube-hosted videos, the YouTube video ID (as seen in YouTube URLs) may also be filled in.
